# LLM Wiki — markdown conventions (`wiki/`)

## Frontmatter

Use YAML frontmatter on hub and topic pages when helpful:

- `title` — display title (can differ from filename).
- `tags` — list of short labels for grouping.
- `aliases` — optional alternate titles for linking.

## Wikilinks

- Link to wiki pages: `[[Page Name]]` or `[[folder/Page Name]]` if you use subfolders.
- Link to sources under `.raw/`: use readable paths, e.g. `[[../.raw/category/file]]` or markdown links ``[`label`](path)`` when wikilinks to dot-folders are awkward.

## Callouts (Obsidian)

Use sparingly for scanability:

```markdown
> [!note] Title
> Body text.
```

Common types: `note`, `tip`, `warning`, `quote`.

## Structure

- Start with a one-paragraph summary, then sections.
- Prefer descriptive filenames: `Topic - Aspect.md` or `topic-aspect.md`; stay consistent within the vault.
